==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} [[ierarchie]] from {{etyl|la}} [[hierarchia]] from {{etyl|grc}} [[ἱεραρχής]] from [[ἱερεύς]] (priest) and [[ἀρχή]] (rule).  Compare {{etyl|fr}} ''[[hiérarchie]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈhaɪə.ɹɑː.kɪ/|/ˈhaɪɹ.ɑːɹ.kɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"haI@r\A:kI/|/"haIr\=A:r\=kI/}}
* {{audio|en-us-hierarchy.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|hierarchies}}

# A body of authoritative [[official]]s organized in [[nested]] [[rank]]s.
# Any group of objects ranked so that every one but the topmost is subordinate to a specified one above it.

